description:
Virtual Typex - A simulation of the British Typex cipher machine
Typex were rotor based, cipher machines which were developed in the U.K. from 1934 onwards. It was based on the commercial German Enigma machine but with a few changes which were made to increase its security.
They were used to send and receive messages for the British during WW2, but also due to its compatibility with Enigma, at Bletchley Park to decipher Enigma messages once the day key had been retrieved using the Bombes.
title: Virtual Typex
